==Awards and nominations==
{{Infobox Musician Awards
| name = Velvet Revolver
| awards = 2
| nominations = 2
| award1 = [[Billboard Music Award]]s
| award1W = 0
| award1N = 1
| award2 = [[Grammy Award]]s
| award2W = 1
| award2N = 0
| award3 = [[Kerrang! Awards]]
| award3W = 1
| award3N = 0
| award4 = [[Radio Music Awards]]
| award4W = 0
| award4N = 1
}}
Velvet Revolver have received one [[Grammy Award]]. The band won the Grammy when "[[Slither (song)|Slither]]" was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Hard Rock Performance|Best Hard Rock Performance]] in 2005. The song "[[Fall to Pieces (Velvet Revolver song)|Fall to Pieces]]" received a nomination for Song of the Year/Rock Radio [[Radio Music Awards|Radio Music Award]] in 2005. The band won the Best International Newcomer [[Kerrang! Awards|Kerrang! Award]] in 2004 while they were nominated for a Rock Artist of the Year [[Billboard Music Award]] in 2005.

;Billboard Music Awards
The [[Billboard Music Award]]s were awarded annually by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine.<ref name="RCA BMA">{{Cite web | last =  | first =  | title = News Archive | publisher = [[RCA Records]] | date = November 29, 2005 | url = http://www.rcarecords.com/news_archive6.html}}</ref>

